        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-08-24 18:20:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> @Jessica, if the file is not found, does it consider latest by default or shall I create also such file in the master branch?\n\nIf the file is not found, the job will fail if container-tag-method is \"yaml-file\" and the file is not there.. \nBut, i think you might like this option better now which got merged today:\nhttps://gerrit.linuxfoundation.org/infra/c/releng/global-jjb/+/65163\n\nThis way, you dont need a yaml file.. .you can just set \"container-tag-method: stream\" in your release file and it will pick the stream value in your job..",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "7f1669c98e85e6dae942deabc2e8aad28eb77e1b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1215,
          "name": "Morgan Richomme",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "morgan.richomme@orange.com",
          "username": "mrichomme"
        },
        "author_role": "CI_BOT",
        "timestamp": "2020-08-25 06:09:19.000000000",
        "message": "Abandoned\n\nnot needed as releng jjb supports stream directive https://gerrit.linuxfoundation.org/infra/c/releng/global-jjb/+/65163",
        "patchset_number": 1
      }
    ]
